'''Jack''' was brought into the ER after being in a car that was hit by another car.

==History==
Jack wanted to go get ice cream and asked his brother, Dylan, to take him. They went out, but on the road, they were hit by a car driven by [[Brooke James]]. They were taken to [[Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital]], where Jack's injuries were assessed to be minor, while Dylan had mesenteric stranding, indicating injury to the mesentery. The doctors asked for the names of their parents so they could be contacted, but Dylan, fearing that he'd be in trouble, told Jack not to tell them. He was taken in for laparoscopic surgery, but they ultimately had to open him up to repair the damage. While he was in surgery, Jack gave [[Miranda Bailey]] Dylan's cell phone, which she used to call their parents. After his surgery, they came to Dylan's bedside.

==Relationships==
===Familial===
Jack lives with his parents and his older brother, Dylan. The two brothers appear to get along well. When Dylan asked Jack to be a brick wall and not tell the doctors their parents' names, he agreed.

==Notes and Trivia==
*He was 7 at the time of his hospitalization.
